p my grades in school. I reached the turning point eventually, focused on school and worked on my story in my freetime. I stopped working on it at some point, due to the lack of knowledge and resources, but at that time it was already very clear to me, that being creative, whether by developing stories or by painting, was exactly what I was going to do all my life.</p><p>I studied communication design and graduated in August 2012 with a Bachelor of Arts title. I learned what it takes to be a designer, other than just illustrating, and my internship at YLF Design gave me great insights into webdesign. My passion to illustrate and paint - especially digitally - never waned, and I hope I will be able to be part of great creations in the future.</p><p>Please visit my Deviantart account for more artworks and descriptions!<a href=\"http://paranosc.deviantart.com/\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;&nbsp; paranosc.deviantart</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>I\'m available for commissions</strong> in the fields of illustrations, digital paintings, webdesign &amp; final artworks, photography retouch and corporate design.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Vita</p><p>Name: Sarah Raaber</p><p>Birthdate: January 18th, 1988</p><p>Nationality: german</p><p>Languages: German (motherlanguage), English (fluently)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Education:</p><p>2012 - today: Freelance Illustrator and Graphicdesigner</p><p>2011- 2012: Internship at YLF Design in Wiesbaden</p><p>2008 – 2012: Communication design at Hochschule Rhein-Main college in Wiesbaden</p><p>2005 – 2007: Technical diploma, department design at Kerschensteinerschule in Wiesbaden</p><p>2004 – 2005: Ten months high school in Florida, USA</p><p>1998 – 2004: Academic high school (Rheingau-Gymnasium and Hildegardis Realschule)</p><p>1994 – 1998: Elementary school Rabanus-Maurus in Oestrich-Winkel</p>\";s:7:\"summary\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:2433:\"<p>Hi! My name is Sarah aka Paranosc, welcome to my online portfolio.</p>\n<p>I was born on January 18th, 1988 in Wiesbaden, Germany. I was raised in an average family, with no artists whatsoever. Considering my fathers talent to sketch warships and tanks, I guess I got my early passion for drawing from him. Throughout my entire life I\'ve been trying to improve my skills, getting inspiration from all kinds of other artworks, as well as games and movies. At the age of 14 I started writing on a story, which I immediately got addicted to. I got lost in thoughts, not being able to keep up my grades in school. I reached the turning point eventually, focused on school and worked on my story in my freetime. I stopped working on it at some point, due to the lack of knowledge and resources, but at that time it was already very clear to me, that being creative, whether by developing stories or by painting, was exactly what I was going to do all my life.</p>\n<p>I studied communication design and graduated in August 2012 with a Bachelor of Arts title. I learned what it takes to be a designer, other than just illustrating, and my internship at YLF Design gave me great insights into webdesign. My passion to illustrate and paint - especially digitally - never waned, and I hope I will be able to be part of great creations in the future.</p>\n<p>Please visit my Deviantart account for more artworks and descriptions!<a href=\"http://paranosc.deviantart.com/\" target=\"_blank\">   paranosc.deviantart</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>I\'m available for commissions</strong> in the fields of illustrations, digital paintings, webdesign &amp; final artworks, photography retouch and corporate design.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Vita</p>\n<p>Name: Sarah Raaber</p>\n<p>Birthdate: January 18th, 1988</p>\n<p>Nationality: german</p>\n<p>Languages: German (motherlanguage), English (fluently)</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Education:</p>\n<p>2012 - today: Freelance Illustrator and Graphicdesigner</p>\n<p>2011- 2012: Internship at YLF Design in Wiesbaden</p>\n<p>2008 – 2012: Communication design at Hochschule Rhein-Main college in Wiesbaden</p>\n<p>2005 – 2007: Technical diploma, department design at Kerschensteinerschule in Wiesbaden</p>\n<p>2004 – 2005: Ten months high school in Florida, USA</p>\n<p>1998 – 2004: Academic high school (Rheingau-Gymnasium and Hildegardis Realschule)</p>\n<p>1994 – 1998: Elementary school Rabanus-Maurus in Oestrich-Winkel</p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:0:{}s:11:\"field_image\";a:0:{}}',0,1427584480,1),('field:node:85','a:5:{s:4:\"body\";a:0:{}s:21:\"field_portfolio_image\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:15:{s:3:\"fid\";s:3:\"177\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"4\";s:8:\"filename\";s:18:\"scan_0021_colo.jpg\";s:3:\"uri\";s:36:\"public://graphics/scan_0021_colo.jpg\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:6:\"546261\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"timestamp\";s:10:\"1357919542\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:0:{}s:16:\"image_dimensions\";a:2:{s:5:\"width\";s:3:\"700\";s:6:\"height\";s:4:\"1048\";}s:3:\"alt\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"width\";s:3:\"700\";s:6:\"height\";s:4:\"1048\";}}}s:27:\"field_portfolio_description\";a:0:{}s:16:\"field_image_type\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:5:\"value\";s:6:\"Scraps\";}}}s:23:\"field_front_page_sticky\";a:0:{}}',0,1427584486,1),('field:node:86','a:5:{s:4:\"body\";a:0:{}s:21:\"field_portfolio_image\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:15:{s:3:\"fid\";s:3:\"178\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"4\";s:8:\"filename\";s:15:\"scan_0022_b.jpg\";s:3:\"uri\";s:33:\"public://graphics/scan_0022_b.jpg\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:6:\"518705\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"timestamp\";s:10:\"1357919566\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:0:{}s:16:\"image_dimensions\";a:2:{s:5:\"width\";s:4:\"1200\";s:6:\"height\";s:3:\"900\";}s:3:\"alt\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"width\";s:4:\"1200\";s:6:\"height\";s:3:\"900\";}}}s:27:\"field_portfolio_description\";a:0:{}s:16:\"field_image_type\";a:1:{s:3:\