INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','article',0,42,42,'und',0,'<p><strong>Liability for Content</strong></p><p>We make every effort to keep the information on our Web site current, but accept no liability whatsoever for the content provided. Pursuant to §7 par. 1 of TMG (German Tele-Media Act), the law limits our responsibility as a service provider to our own content on these Web pages.<br>According to §§8 to 10 of TMG, we are not obligated to monitor third party information provided or stored on our Web site. However, we shall promptly remove any content upon becoming aware that it violates the law. Our liability in such an instance shall commence at the time we become aware of the respective violation.</p><p><strong>Liability for Links</strong></p><p>Our site contains links to third-party Web sites. We have no influence whatsoever on the information on these Web sites and accept no guaranty for its correctness. The content of such third-party sites is the responsibility of the respective owners/providers.<br>At the time third-party Web sites were linked to ours, we found NO GROUNDS WHATSOEVER of any likely contravention of the law. We shall promptly delete a link upon becoming aware that it violates the law.</p><p><strong>Copyrights</strong></p><p>The content and works provided on these Web pages are governed by the copyright laws of Germany. Duplication, processing, distribution, or any form of commercialization of such material beyond the scope of the copyright law shall require the prior written consent of its respective author or creator.</p><p><strong>Data Protection</strong></p><p>Please be aware that there are inherent security risks in transmitting data, such as e-mails, via the Internet, because it is impossible to safeguard completely against unauthorized access by third parties. Nevertheless, we shall safeguard your data, subject to this limitation. In particular, personal information will be transmitted via the Internet only if it does not infringe upon third-party rights, unless the respective party has given its prior consent in view of such security risks. Accordingly, as the Web site provider, we shall not be held liable for any damages incurred as a consequence of such security risks or for any related acts of omission on our part.<br>We oppose the use of any available contact information by a third party for sending unsolicited advertisements. As the Web site provider, we reserve the express right to take legal action against unsolicited mailing or e-mailing of spam and other similar advertising materials.</p><p><strong>Content</strong></p><p>Sarah Raaber<br>Blücherstraße 38<br>65195 Wiesbaden<br>Germany<br><a href=\"mailto:sarah.raaber@gmx.de\">sarah.raaber@gmx.de</a><br>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Webdesign</strong></p><p>Sebastian Gurlt<br><a href=\"mailto:sebastian.gurlt@googlemail.com\">sebastian.gurlt@googlemail.com</a></p>','','full_html'),('node','article',0,49,49,'und',0,'<p>Hi! My name is Sarah aka Paranosc, welcome to my online portfolio.</p><p>I was born on January 18th, 1988 in Wiesbaden, Germany. I was raised in an average family, with no artists whatsoever. Considering my fathers talent to sketch warships and tanks, I guess I got my early passion for drawing from him. Throughout my entire life I\'ve been trying to improve my skills, getting inspiration from all kinds of other artworks, as well as games and movies. At the age of 14 I started writing on a story, which I immediately got addicted to. I got lost in thoughts, not being able to keep up my grades in school. I reached the turning point eventually, focused on school and worked on my story in my freetime. I stopped working on it at some point, due to the lack of knowledge and resources, but at that time it was already very clear to me, that being creative, whether by developing stories or by painting, was exactly what I was going to do all my life.</p><p>I studied communication design and graduated in August 2012 with a Bachelor of Arts title. I learned what it takes to be a designer, other than just illustrating, and my internship at YLF Design gave me great insights into webdesign. My passion to illustrate and paint - especially digitally - never waned, and I hope I will be able to be part of great creations in the future.</p><p>Please visit my Deviantart account for more artworks and descriptions!<a href=\"http://paranosc.deviantart.com/\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;&nbsp; paranosc.deviantart</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>I\'m available for commissions</strong> in the fields of illustrations, digital paintings, webdesign &amp; final artworks, photography retouch and corporate design.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Vita</p><p>Name: Sarah Raaber</p><p>Birthdate: January 18th, 1988</p><p>Nationality: german</p><p>Languages: German (motherlanguage), English (fluently)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Education:</p><p>2012 - today: Freelance Illustrator and Graphicdesigner</p><p>2011- 2012: Internship at YLF Design in Wiesbaden</p><p>2008 – 2012: Communication design at Hochschule Rhein-Main college in Wiesbaden</p><p>2005 – 2007: Technical diploma, department design at Kerschensteinerschule in Wiesbaden</p><p>2004 – 2005: Ten months high school in Florida, USA</p><p>1998 – 2004: Academic high school (Rheingau-Gymnasium and Hildegardis Realschule)</p><p>1994 – 1998: Elementary school Rabanus-Maurus in Oestrich-Winkel</p>','','full_html'),('node','project',0,108,108,'und',0,'<p><em>The art of looking into yourself.</em></p><p>To look into myself...</p><p>To work with myself... To analyze and understand myself...</p><p>Hmm...</p><p>\"Ego Art\"... To put myself into an artwork. Just like that.</p><p>So this time, I\'m the object... <strong>Great</strong>.</p><p>So, who am I? What makes me <strong>me</strong>?</p><p>....</p><p>And <strong>what the hell</strong> do I feel?</p><p>...</p><p>I have no idea how to do this. I used to draw what I feel. In a very little original, metaphorical way. And now?</p><p>Now I\'m way too confused for that.</p><p>Confusion... In fact, that could be it already.</p><p>Negative feelings are way stronger than positive ones anyway. So why not work with that? We have plenty of those to offer.</p><p>My following <em>Seven</em> came along with me for a while. Time to put them into the front.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Now, how to do this?</p><p>Photography is out of question. Cameras hate me too much. And I <strong>suck</strong> at photography.</p><p>Silhouettes... Not exactly showing myself, but not hiding either. Sounds good.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>What else? The question of colors. Strong feelings need strong colors. Red, Orange, everything that <strong>burns</strong>. Should hurt a little. I also like wallpapers. Streetstyle, striking graphics and yet detailed.</p><p>With this assignment I could finally apply it all and even find a new passion.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>And I myself...</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>... I\'m really not <em>that</em> bad.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The Seven:</strong></p><p>- Bondage</p><p>- Decay</p><p>- Intoxication</p><p>- Vengeance</p><p>- Leakage</p><p>- Outbreak</p><p>- Burst</p>','','full_html'),('node','project',0,109,109,'und',0,'<p>Illustrations for a fictive book for teens at the age of 14 - 16. The theme of this book was the biography of a historical person and the era they lived in.</p>\r\n<p>I chose a mixed style of analog outlines and digital coloration to create a combination of old-fashioned children&#39;s books and modern generation.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','project',0,110,110,'und',0,'<p>The topic of this poster project<em> </em><em>&quot;Alles Liebe?&quot; (&quot;All Love?&quot;)</em> was to show how students might feel about their time in college and how they experience it, wheather they hate it, love it, have mixed feelings or don&#39;t even think about it.&nbsp;</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','project',0,111,111,'und',0,'<p>A poster for and about my internship in 2012 with 3D effect, using a few of the agencys logo designs as planets.Bottom left is a sentence which, in my opinion, represents their philosophy and the way they work and think. The scale on the bottom right shows the different design fields they offer and how much each of them is covered (at least from what I\'ve experienced in those 6 months). In between there\'s keywords like Pasta, Coffee, Acton Figures etc., to relate to my personal memory and relationship to the agency, furthermore what I think makes them who they are.The idea behind the universe was to represent the depth and variety of the agencys service.</p><p>This project was part of my six months internship at <a href=\"http://youlookfor.us/\" target=\"_blank\">YLF Design</a>.</p>','','full_html'),('node','project',0,112,112,'und',0,'<p>For our final thesis my friend and colleague Justyna Matuszewska and I made this <em>Photoshop CS5 Guide for students</em>.</p><p>The idea was to create an assistance for design students, who haven\'t worked with Photoshop before. The program is essential for every designer, and with its wide spread of options and applications, this guide would quickly help beginners to learn how to use the basics of Photoshop CS5. Since there\'s already a number of guides, what makes our guide better than others? Our research showed us, that many of the existing guides are either too voluminous, use very bad examples, or didn\'t cover topics like illustrations and graphics. Our job was to filter important topics to receive a light handbook and practise every tutorial using good photography and artworks.</p><p>In addition to the book, we created an online platform for students, where they could upload their works, give feeback and their own tutorials.</p><p>Content of our thesis:</p><p>- Research<br>- Conception<br>- Logo Design<br>- Guide Design &amp; Tutorials<br>- Webdesign<br>- Production</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','full_html'),('node','project',0,117,117,'und',0,'<p>Price list for <em>Weingut (winery) Peth</em>. The design should differ from previous price lists and have a modern and clean look.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.weinshop-peth.de/\" target=\"_blank\">www.weinshop-peth.de</a></p><p>This project was part of my six months internship at <a href=\"http://youlookfor.us/\" target=\"_blank\">YLF Design</a>.</p>','','full_html'),('node','project',0,118,118,'und',0,'<p>Photography retouch of the Vandeyk bike series <em>Nightstream Road</em>. The cold blue-cyan and strong, saturated colors were both crucial and had to match the previous series.</p><p><a href=\"http://vandeyk.de/\" target=\"_blank\">www.vandeyk.de</a></p><p>This project was part of my six months internship at <a href=\"http://youlookfor.us/\" target=\"_blank\">YLF Design</a>.</p>','','full_html'),('node','project',0,119,119,'und',0,'<p>Final artwork for <em>We Are</em>, a journal website for a worldtour to china by bike. The journey was to be documented using videos, regular reports and a route display. With a given basic layout, my job was to find solutions, create subsites and give the final touch.</p><p><a href=\"http://wearetraveling.de/\" target=\"_blank\">www.wearetraveling.de</a></p><p>This project was part of my six months internship at <a href=\"http://youlookfor.us/\" target=\"_blank\">YLF Design</a>.</p>','','full_html'),('node','project',0,142,142,'und',0,'<p>Photo retouch for the singer Barry L\'Affair.</p><p>The overall style was to match his type of music: funky with a little bit of rock\'n\'roll. His idea was to create three different color schemes. Pink to match his logo, golden to recreate his previous pictures and blue/green to get a whole new look &amp; feel.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"http://www.barrylaffair.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.barrylaffair.com</a></p>','','full_html');
